# Post-Commit Report

After every successful `git commit`, run `git log -1 --format='%H%n%an <%ae>%n%ai%n%s%n%b'` and display a summary to the user **BEFORE pushing**:

- **Commit hash** (full)
- **Author** (name and email)
- **Date**
- **Commit message** (subject + body)
- **Branch** name

Wait for user confirmation before running `git push`. This gives the user a chance to review and amend if needed.
